<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002538.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sunnbeard</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Greetings!  I have a lvl 19 Troll warrior. A cleric told me the other day that the damage my warrior deals will double at lvl 20. I had not heard this before, and it seems pretty unlikely. I have a lvl 29 Necro also, and his damage did not double at 20, but I'm wondering now if it is because he is a pure caster. Can someone confirm whether this is true or not?  Also, I (stupidly) neglected my two hand slashing skill because I was convinced I wanted double wield. Now my two hand slash is like 25...what is the best way to increase it (without dying)? Thanks for your help!<P>Katkum Lvl 19 Troll Warrior</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Zubaz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Im not exactly a 20+ warrior but nobody else has responded yet so... from what i have read on this board yes your str or dmg? cap comes off and you can do more damage then you have been doing now for the last 19 levels..im not exactly sure if its 2x the amount of damage but i cant wait to get there either =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Lasae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well I guess I qualify at 43  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"><P>Your damage will not double BUT it will for one be uncapped when calculating in your damage, simply said, having lots of strength as a troll warrior will allow your weapons to hit beyond the 2*(weapon damage) + 1.  When you reach 50 though you will be hitting for double damage or (4*weapons dmg) so a Langseax *can* hit for 24 dmg, as a 6dmg sword.  Having more strength you'll notice a more significant improvement while wielding a 2h, and you should wield a 2h sword till 30, when your duel wield, double attack, and 1h slashing reach 150 skill, when you'll begin to quad attack.<P>Best bet, just pump as many skill points as you have into it, raise your dex (higher dex, faster you learn a weapon), try and get a 2h with lower delay (get a Gigantic Zweihander if you can or a Forged Two Hander or FS Two Hander).  <P>Your strength abilities at this point give you an advantage in that you can hit for more damage now, than someone with less strength, but that kind of caps at level 50.<P><P>------------------<BR>Lasae Leniyersa<BR>Vallon Zek<BR>Emerald Warriorette of the 43rd Season <BR><I>Master Fletcher: 192</I><BR><I>Average Archery Skill: 64</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Noreal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">You will see very little increase going from 19 to 20 with 1hs. <P>However, using a 2hs weapon with a base damage of over 14 will give you quite the increase when you ding to 20.<P>As a troll, you've most likely been slashing for more than 2*base+1 for a few levels now, hitting for 14's and 15's with a 6 base weapon, and the margin of damage will increase as you gain more skill, until you are able to hit for 4*base or so at 50. With a 2h, this margin is even more pronounced.<P>The easiest way to get it up is to join a group where you will be a secondary tank and just keep at it. You should be able to get a good 50pts a night, or more.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sunnbeard</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thanks much for the help!  I appreciate it.<P>Katkum</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
